         <notesStmt>
            <note>
               <p>A digital transcription of the Naples 1492 edition of Mishnah with Maimonides' commentary in medieval Hebrew translation</p>
               <p>Images accessed through the National Library of Israel at 
                  <ref target="https://www.nli.org.il/en/books/NNL_ALEPH001143297/NLI?volumeItem=3"
                     >https://www.nli.org.il/en/books/NNL_ALEPH001143297/NLI?volumeItem=3</ref></p>
               <p>Automated page segmentation and text recognition utilizes 
                  <ref target="https://github.com/mittagessen/kraken">kraken</ref>, 
                  as implemented by the <ref target="https://gitlab.com/scripta/escriptorium">eScriptorium</ref>
                  platform as hosted by the <ref target="https://www.ephe.psl.eu/">EPHE, Paris, France</ref></p>
               <p>This is a trial release (version 0.1) of the whole text of the
                  Mishnah according to Kaufmann, excepting Bava Qamma, Bava Metsi'a, 
                  and Bava Batra, for which hand transcription exists under the id number
                  1143297. Abbreviations have not been expanded. 
                  Only minimal incorporation of marginalia and corrections was possible.</p>
            </note>
